'## ⚙ 2026-04-04 — Session 10: Launch-GUI.bat Enterprise Enhancements — PS7 Detection, Exec Policy Diagnostics, Launch Logging, CFRMenu',
'',
'### Launch-GUI.bat v2604.B1.v1.0 (major enhancement)',
'- **PowerShell 7 Detection & Installation:**',
'  - Detects PS7 via: 1) `where pwsh` check, 2) Registry (`HKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\PowerShell\\7\\Install`), 3) File existence (`%ProgramFiles%\\PowerShell\\7\\pwsh.exe`)',
'  - If not detected, displays 7-second prompt: "Press Y to install PowerShell 7 automatically" via winget',
'  - Winget command: `winget install --id Microsoft.Powershell --source winget --silent --accept-package-agreements --accept-source-agreements`',
'  - On successful install, auto-restarts Launch-GUI.bat with PS7 available',
'- **Execution Policy Detection & Solution Menu:**',
'  - Detects `Restricted` execution policy (blocks all scripts)',
'  - Presents 6-option menu with risk assessment and scope details for each solution:',
'    1. Bypass (Current Session Only) — ✓ RECOMMENDED — LOW risk, session-only, no admin',
'    2. RemoteSigned (CurrentUser) — BALANCED — MEDIUM risk, user-scope, no admin',
'    3. RemoteSigned (LocalMachine) — ENTERPRISE — MEDIUM risk, machine-scope, requires admin',
'    4. Unrestricted (CurrentUser) — PERMISSIVE — HIGH risk, user-scope, no admin',
'    5. View Manual Instructions — Links to Microsoft docs',
'    6. Continue Anyway — Sets bypass flag for session',
'  - Solution menu includes: risk level, scope, admin requirement, use case description',
'  - If bypass selected, all PowerShell calls use `-ExecutionPolicy Bypass` flag via `%USE_BYPASS_FLAG%` variable',
'- **Comprehensive Launch Logging:**',
'  - Logs every launch to `logs/Main-GUI_BATCH-LOG.log` (CSV format, UTF-8)',
'  - 14 telemetry fields collected via Get-LaunchTelemetry.psm1:',
'    1. Timestamp (YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS)',
'    2. BatchName (Launch-GUI.bat)',
'    3. VersionTag (2604.B1.v1.0)',
'    4. MachineName',
'    5. Username',
'    6. IPAddress (filters APIPA 169.254.x.x and loopback)',
'    7. BatchPath (full path to batch file)',
'    8. SystemVolume (drive letter)',
'    9. SystemVolFreeSpace (GB)',
'    10. MemoryUsedOfTotal (used GB / total GB)',
'    11. CPULoad (%, averaged over 500ms)',
'    12. GPULoad (%, from Performance Counter or N/A)',
'    13. TotalProcesses (count)',
'    14. IsAdmin (TRUE/FALSE)',
'  - CSV header auto-created on first launch',
'  - Each subsequent launch appends one CSV line',
'- **First Launch Detection & CFRMenu Trigger:**',
'  - Detects first launch when `logs/Main-GUI_BATCH-LOG.log` doesn\'t exist',
'  - Sets `FIRST_LAUNCH=TRUE` flag',
'  - Auto-launches `Launch-CFRMenu.bat` (First Run Configuration Menu) with 3-second countdown message',
'  - After CFRMenu exits, proceeds to normal Launch-GUI.bat menu',
'',
'### Launch-CFRMenu.bat v2604.B1.v1.0 (new file)',
'- **Purpose:** First-time user configuration and diagnostic menu',
'- **Auto-triggered:** On first Launch-GUI.bat run (when log file missing)',
'- **Manual launch:** `Launch-CFRMenu.bat` anytime',
'- **Menu Structure:**',
'  - **PRE-FLIGHT CHECKS & FIXES (1-5):**',
'    1. Run Full Prerequisite Check (Test-Prerequisites.ps1)',
'    2. Repair Module Import Paths (Repair-ModulePaths.ps1)',
'    3. Test PowerShell Compatibility (PS 5.1 vs PS 7 feature check)',
'    4. Validate SIN Governance Registry (integrity check, count patterns)',
'    5. Initialize CronAiAthon Scheduler (first-run setup)',
'  - **SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS & REPORTS (6-10):**',
'    6. Generate Full System Report (Export-SystemReport.ps1 to HTML)',
'    7. Export Module Dependency Graph (opens Dependency-Visualisation.html)',
'    8. Run Network Connectivity Tests (DNS/HTTP/Azure/GitHub endpoints)',
'    9. Check Disk Space & Clean Temp Files (with optional temp cleanup)',
'    10. Baseline Performance Metrics (capture current CPU/RAM/processes to ~REPORTS/)',
'  - **SECURITY & COMPLIANCE (11-14):**',
'    11. Run SIN Pattern Scanner (Invoke-SINPatternScanner.ps1 for all 18 blocking patterns)',
'    12. Audit Execution Policy Configuration (all scopes + effective policy)',
'    13. Check for Hardcoded Secrets (scan for API_KEY/PASSWORD/TOKEN/etc in code)',
'    14. Validate File Encodings (UTF-8 BOM check for Unicode files, PS 5.1 compatibility)',
'  - **QUICK LAUNCHER WIDGETS (A-F):**',
'    - A) Launch-GUI-quik_jnr.bat (fast startup)',
'    - B) Launch-GUI-slow_snr.bat (full checks)',
'    - C) Launch-SandboxInteractive.bat',
'    - D) Launch-ChaosTest.bat',
'    - E) Launch-CarGame.bat',
'    - F) View-Config.ps1',
'  - **Exit:** Option 0 returns to main Launch-GUI.bat menu',
'- **UI:** ASCII box-drawing characters (`╔═╗║╚═╝`) for professional menu appearance',
'- **Persistence:** Menu redisplays after each option, allowing multiple diagnostics in one session',
'',
'### modules/Get-LaunchTelemetry.psm1 (new module)',
'- **Exported Function:** `Get-LaunchTelemetry`',
'- **Parameters:** `-BatchName`, `-VersionTag`, `-BatchPath`',
'- **Collects 14 telemetry fields:**',
'  - Timestamp: `Get-Date -Format "yyyyMMdd-HHmmss"`',
'  - Machine/User: `$env:COMPUTERNAME`, `$env:USERNAME`',
'  - IP: `Get-NetIPAddress -AddressFamily IPv4` filtered (excludes APIPA 169.254.x.x, loopback 127.0.0.1); fallback to `ipconfig` parsing',
'  - Path: BatchPath parameter (full path to launcher scripts/Test-Prerequisites.ps1 (new script)',
'- **10 Validation Checks:**',
'  1. PowerShell version >= 5.1',
'  2. CronAiAthon-EventLog.psm1 exists',
'  3. CronAiAthon-Pipeline.psm1 exists',
'  4. CronAiAthon-Scheduler.psm1 exists',
'  5. PwShGUI-Theme.psm1 exists',
'  6. PwShGUI-NetworkTools.psm1 exists',
'  7. PwShGUI-SecretStore.psm1 exists',
'  8. Logs directory exists (creates if missing)',
'  9. Disk space > 1GB free',
'  10. Network connectivity (ping 8.8.8.8)',
'- **Output:** Formatted table with ✓ PASS / ⚠ WARN / ✗ FAIL status and colored console output',
'- **Exit Code:** 0 if all pass, 1 if any failures',
'- **Use Case:** Option 1 in CFRMenu, pre-deployment validation',
'',
'### scripts/Repair-ModulePaths.ps1 (new script)',
'- **Purpose:** Add PowerShellGUI\\modules to PSModulePath',
'- **Actions:**',
'  1. Validates modules directory exists',
'  2. Checks if already in `$env:PSModulePath`',
'  3. Adds to current session if missing',
'  4. Prompts: "Do you want to persist this change to your user profile? [Y/N]"',
'  5. If Y, updates User environment variable (no admin required): `[Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("PSModulePath", $newPath, "User")`',
'  6. Validates repair by importing test module (CronAiAthon-EventLog.psm1)',
'- **Output:** Success message with green text or error details',
'- **Use Case:** Option 2 in CFRMenu, fixes "module not found" errors',
'',
'### scripts/Export-SystemReport.ps1 (new script)',
'- **Purpose:** Generate comprehensive HTML system diagnostic report',
'- **7 Data Collection Phases:**',
'  1. **OS Info:** Caption, Version, Architecture, BuildNumber, InstallDate, LastBootTime (Win32_OperatingSystem)',
'  2. **Computer System:** Name, Domain, Manufacturer, Model, TotalPhysicalMemory, Processors (Win32_ComputerSystem)',
'  3. **Processors:** Name, Cores, LogicalProcessors, MaxClockSpeed for each CPU (Win32_Processor)',
'  4. **Disks:** DeviceID, VolumeName, FileSystem, Size, FreeSpace for all logical drives (Win32_LogicalDisk filter DriveType=3)',
'  5. **Network:** Name, Status, LinkSpeed, MacAddress, IPv4Address for up adapters only (Get-NetAdapter + Get-NetIPAddress)',
'  6. **PowerShell Modules:** Name, Version, Path (first 50 modules only for performance)',
'  7. **Execution Policies:** Scope and Policy for all 5 scopes (Get-ExecutionPolicy -List)',
'- **HTML Features:**',
'  - Gradient header (purple/blue: `linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%)`)',
